    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Corrections</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Correction holds that Aug 9 editorial about Texas executions erred in saying that Supreme Court has ruled that executing minors under age 16 violates Constitution</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>An editorial on Wednesday about Texas executions erred in saying that the Supreme Court has ruled that executing minors under age 16 violates the Constitution. In 1988, in a 5-to-4 decision overturning an Oklahoma statute, four justices agreed that executing a person who was 15 years old at the time a crime was committed would be unconstitutional; a fifth justice concurred on narrower grounds.</p>
      </block>
